igament injury?","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035865,0.056618,0.072619,0.088119,0.096104,0.10537,0.11009,0.10621,0.10564,0.10521,0.074892,0.043261],"unified_progress":[0.044766,0.072034,0.066814,0.10454,0.10904,0.10578,0.10428,0.10005,0.091969,0.083716,0.06643,0.050587]},{"section":17,"text":"Yeah, that's it!","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.12019,0.095604,0.088895,0.079913,0.079774,0.080906,0.082064,0.088527,0.07778,0.052193,0.053427,0.10073],"unified_progress":[0.21434,0.081023,0.06621,0.065616,0.074636,0.072707,0.10518,0.079957,0.075901,0.059594,0.054402,0.050431]},{"section":18,"text":"It's when the scaphoid bone looks like a spilled teaccup on the X-ray.","dimension":7,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051759,0.061308,0.076793,0.091545,0.098063,0.10278,0.10339,0.09709,0.094035,0.09429,0.075474,0.053468],"unified_progress":[0.061454,0.080286,0.065765,0.10138,0.10331,0.10556,0.098486,0.094505,0.086641,0.079705,0.067016,0.055897]},{"section":19,"text":"That's a big clue pointing towards a specific type of wrist injury.","dimension":0,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039915,0.082622,0.094539,0.10222,0.10319,0.10196,0.097534,0.088169,0.08468,0.079059,0.071223,0.054894],"unified_progress":[0.044063,0.075988,0.091416,0.098549,0.10319,0.099922,0.0981,0.091178,0.086463,0.078278,0.071822,0.061036]},{"section":20,"text":"So, putting all these pieces together\u2014the way he fell, the symptoms, and the X-ray finding\u2014it really seems like we're dealing with a scapholunate ligament injury.","dimension":3,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029822,0.049341,0.063046,0.072649,0.077765,0.081203,0.083103,0.082634,0.086056,0.098016,0.1308,0.14556],"unified_progress":[0.033697,0.050936,0.062646,0.072653,0.076684,0.084657,0.084828,0.091938,0.096434,0.099625,0.11372,0.13219]},{"section":21,"text":"But wait, let's not jump to conclusions too quickly.","dimen